            , and lodge in <placeName id="t18281204-240-crimeloc1270">Perry-street, Somers'-town</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-240-crimeloc1270" type="placeName" value="Perry-street, Somers'-town"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281204-240-crimeloc1270" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-240-off1268 t18281204-240-crimeloc1270"></join>, on the second-floor - Thomas Hewit, the landlord, lives in the house; two young men lived in the back-room, first-floor; two parlours were occupied by other lodgers; I went out about half-past five o'clock in the afternoon of the 2d of October, I locked the door I am quite positive, and left all the property safe in the room; I returned about one o'clock with my husband, and found the door wide open; the lock was half back, it was half out of the box - it appeared as if it had been picked with a false key; I missed the articles stated in the indictment, and saw all of those at Mary-le-bone-office on or about the 20th of October, but I missed more - the prisoner was in custody; he was one of the lodgers in the house, but we were not intimate with him at all, and never visited; he lodged in the back-room first-floor - he called himself a piano-forte maker, out of employ; I have a letter which I received - I do not know the hand-writing - it came by post on Monday.</p>
